All Classes

  • Class Description
    Alien
    Alien object that implements Sprite interface.
    AlienShape
    An alien that can be moved around.
    Barrier
    Barrier object that implements Sprite interface.
    Board
    Board (Model) stores all information about the current state of the game and handles collision detection and player movement.
    Controller
    Controller class that handles communication between View and Model as well as handle the state of the game.
    GameTemplate
    Implementation of TEMPLATE design pattern which involves an abstract class that exposes defined ways/templates to execute its methods.
    KeyPressedMessage
    Key event pressed message.
    KeyPressedValve
    Valve that processes the Key Pressed event message by using the Board's set key down method and setting the appropriate flags for shot and bomb.
    KeyReleasedMessage
    Key event released message.
    KeyReleasedValve
    Valve that processes Key Released event message by using the Board's set key up method and updating.
    Message
    Message interface used to tag classes sent between View and Blocking Queue.
    MoveableImage
    Customized image class that contains an explosion image to be used by the game pieces as well as flags, draw, and set/get for positioning.
    MoveableShape
    A shape that can be moved around.
    NewGameMessage
    New game message.
    NewGameValve
    Valve to process New Game message, initates start over command and creates new aliens and resets speed and visibility.
    Player
    Player class implements the Sprite interface and contains the properties for the player vehicle and methods to read key presses for movement and firing.
    Projectile
    Projectile class that implements Sprite interface to be used as either a player shot or alien bomb.
    RandomSingleton
    Implementation of SINGLETON design pattern which involves a single class which is responsible in creating only one object of itself.
    ShapeIcon
    An icon that contains a moveable shape.
    SpaceInvader
    Space Invaders game implementation using MVC, Command, Facade, Singleton, and Template design patterns for CS151 in SJSU.
    Sprite
    Sprite interface contains the necessary methods to get/set positions of objects, and set visibility.
    SpriteMaker
    Implementation of FACADE design pattern, which hides the complexities of the system and provides an interface to the client for ease of use.
    Valve
    Part of COMMAND design pattern implementation.
    Valve.ValveResponse  
    View
    View provides the user interface and graphics to be displayed for the game.
    ViewUpdateMessage
    View Update Message to be sent during draw time in View.
    ViewUpdateValve
    Valve to process the View Update message sent by View during repaint.
